📚 Day 11 Topic:
React Forms & Controlled Components
1. What is it?

A Form is a collection of inputs that allow users to enter data.

Examples:

Login Form
Registration Form
Contact Form
Search Bar
Feedback Form

React manages form data using state.

2. Why do we need it?

Imagine a login page.

User enters:

Email
Password

React must know:

What user typed
When input changes
When form submits

Without state React cannot track user input.

Real Problem

Normal HTML:

<input type="text">

Browser stores the value.

React prefers:

State stores the value

This gives React full control.

